# v1.5 Phase B — `httpGet` / `httpPost` / `httpClient` primitives

Note: requires outbound network access (https://httpbin.org).

```scalascript
// B.1 — httpGet returns a Response with status, body, headers.
val r1 = httpGet("https://httpbin.org/status/200")
println(r1.status)

// httpGet with custom headers.
val r2 = httpGet("https://httpbin.org/get", Map("X-Foo" -> "bar"))
println(r2.status)

// B.1 — httpPost returns a Response.
val r3 = httpPost("https://httpbin.org/post", "hello")
println(r3.status)

// httpPost with content-type header.
val r4 = httpPost(
  "https://httpbin.org/post",
  "{\"x\":1}",
  Map("Content-Type" -> "application/json")
)
println(r4.status)

// B.2 — httpClient sets base URL for relative paths within the block.
httpClient("https://httpbin.org") {
  val r = httpGet("/status/204")
  println(r.status)
}
```
